Crypto.fxml
    contains TableView and colChart

CryptoController.java
    receives colChart using @FXML
    setupChartColumn() adds "Show Chart" button to each row
    button gets selected Crypto object
    button calls openCryptoChartWindow(crypto)

openCryptoChartWindow()
    opens new JavaFX Stage
    shows loading spinner
    starts Task<List<CryptoPricePoint>>

Task
    calls CryptoChartService.getMarketChart(crypto.getApiid(), 30, "usd")

CryptoChartService.java
    builds CoinGecko URL
    sends HTTP GET request
    receives JSON response
    extracts "prices"
    converts timestamps to LocalDateTime
    creates List<CryptoPricePoint>

CryptoPricePoint.java
    stores one chart point: dateTime + price

CryptoController.java
    receives List<CryptoPricePoint>
    creates CategoryAxis and NumberAxis
    creates LineChart<String, Number>
    converts each CryptoPricePoint into XYChart.Data
    adds all data to XYChart.Series
    adds series to LineChart
    replaces loading screen with the chart


 NEWS FUNCTION


 Crypto.fxml
     adds colNews

 CryptoController.java
     creates News button per crypto row
     gets selected Crypto object
     opens news window
     starts JavaFX Task

 CryptoNewsService.java
     reads GNEWS_API_KEY from .env.local
     calls GNews Search API
     parses JSON articles with Jackson
     returns List<CryptoNewsArticle>

 CryptoNewsArticle.java
     stores title, description, url, imageUrl, publishedAt, sourceName

 CryptoController.java
     creates JavaFX cards
     loads article images into ImageView
     displays cards in ScrollPane